## BUG-UI-004
**Bug Name:** Navigation Menu Overlaps Content  
**Severity:** Medium  
**Priority:** High  
**Frequency:** 100%

**Description:**  
On tablet devices in landscape mode, the navigation menu overlaps the main content area.

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1. Open the site on a tablet in landscape orientation
2. Open the navigation menu
3. Observe overlap with content

**Expected Result:** Menu should push content or appear as an overlay without obscuring important elements

**Actual Result:** Menu covers approximately 40% of the content area

**Environment:** iPad Safari, Android Chrome  
**Screenshot:** [Attached]

---

## BUG-UI-005
**Bug Name:** Color Contrast Issues  
**Severity:** Medium  
**Priority:** Medium  
**Frequency:** 100%

**Description:**  
Text on several buttons has insufficient color contrast, failing WCAG AA accessibility standards.

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1. Navigate to the checkout page
2. Observe "Proceed to Payment" button
3. Run accessibility audit

**Expected Result:** Text contrast ratio should be at least 4.5:1

**Actual Result:** Contrast ratio is 3.2:1

**Environment:** All browsers  
**Accessibility Impact:** Affects users with visual impairmentsClaude is AI and can make mistakes. Please double-check responses. Sonnet 4.5
